# Support Ticket Management API Request Collection

@host = http://localhost:5104

### 1. Create a Support Ticket (Auto-Classified)
# Automatically categorizes and assigns priority based on text keywords.
POST {{host}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_id": "CUST-4001",
  "customer_email": "jane.doe@example.com",
  "customer_name": "Jane Doe",
  "subject": "Cannot log in resetting password locked out credentials",
  "description": "I cannot login to my account. My password keeps failing and I am locked out from credentials.",
  "metadata": {
    "source": "web_form",
    "browser": "Chrome 125.0",
    "device_type": "desktop"
  },
  "auto_classify": true
}

###

### 2. Create a Support Ticket (Manual Override)
# Overrides classification on creation by passing manual fields.
POST {{host}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_id": "CUST-4002",
  "customer_email": "john.jones@example.com",
  "customer_name": "John Jones",
  "subject": "Question about billing costs",
  "description": "Just looking to find the invoice details.",
  "category": "billing_question",
  "priority": "low",
  "metadata": {
    "source": "email",
    "device_type": "mobile"
  },
  "auto_classify": false
}

###

### 3. List All Support Tickets
GET {{host}}/tickets

###

### 4. List Tickets with Combined Filtering
# Filter by category and priority
GET {{host}}/tickets?category=account_access&priority=urgent

###

### 5. Fetch a Ticket by ID
# NOTE: Replace the UUID with a valid ID from the list tickets response
@ticketId = d3b07384-d113-4444-a267-34d650221389
GET {{host}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}

###

### 6. Run Auto-Classification On-Demand
# Re-analyzes text to classify the category/priority
POST {{host}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}/auto-classify

###

### 7. Update Ticket Fields (Manual Override)
# Mutates ticket fields. Manually changing category/priority resets confidence score to 1.0.
PUT {{host}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_progress",
  "assigned_to": "agent_charlie",
  "category": "technical_issue",
  "priority": "high",
  "tags": ["high-priority", "v1.2-bug"]
}

###

### 8. Delete a Ticket
DELETE {{host}}/tickets/{{ticketId}}

###

### =========================================================================
### NEGATIVE TESTS (EXPECTED FAILURES)
### =========================================================================

### 9. Create Ticket - Validation Failures (Should return 400 Bad Request)
# Fails because:
# - customer_email is not a valid email
# - subject is empty
# - description is too short (less than 10 characters)
POST {{host}}/tickets
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_id": "CUST-FAIL",
  "customer_email": "invalid-email-address",
  "customer_name": "Test Failure",
  "subject": "",
  "description": "short",
  "metadata": {
    "source": "web_form",
    "device_type": "desktop"
  }
}

###

### 10. Fetch Non-Existent Ticket (Should return 404 Not Found)
GET {{host}}/tickets/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

###

### 11. Update Non-Existent Ticket (Should return 404 Not Found)
PUT {{host}}/tickets/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "resolved"
}

###

### 12. Delete Non-Existent Ticket (Should return 404 Not Found)
DELETE {{host}}/tickets/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

###

### 13. Auto-Classify Non-Existent Ticket (Should return 404 Not Found)
POST {{host}}/tickets/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/auto-classify

###

### 14. Bulk Import Unsupported File Format (Should return 400 Bad Request)
POST {{host}}/tickets/import
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="invalid_extension.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

customer_id,customer_email
CUST-1,test@test.com
--boundary--

